reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lasted a year and a half
reviews.reviewText: Bought this case and used it everyday for the past year and a half, and today on its 976th drop, the outer shell came off but the inside bit didn't. Case broke but not the phone!!Only problem I ever had with it is once in a blue moon one card would stick inside the sliding door and seem to disappear. Once I found where to check though, it didn't matter. Really good case.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars This product is a very sturdy
reviews.reviewText: This product was received very fast and when I took it out of the packaging, it fit onto my phone like it was painted on. It was a very good fit and everything worked perfectly. The door in the back where I put my ID is very easy to open and the crisscross texture makes it almost impossible to slip in my hand. It is missing a couple of things I would like but I knew they were not included when I purchased it. I would buy this again. Especially for the kids.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The case gives good protection for your phone. I’ve dropped it a few times and my phone is still intact. The card slot holds 2 cards. However, the slider that covers the credit card slot is somewhat flimsy. The sliding mechanism isn’t always smooth and it broke completely after a few months.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The Nvollnoe iPhone 14 Case with Card Holder is a perfect blend of style and functionality. The heavy-duty dual-layer design provides robust protection against shocks and drops, ensuring my iPhone 14 stays safe and sound. The hidden card slot, a standout feature, adds a touch of convenience without compromising the slim and sleek profile.The case's compatibility with wireless charging is a welcome bonus, eliminating the need to remove it for a quick power-up. The precise cutouts and responsive buttons make for a seamless user experience, and the raised edges around the camera and screen offer additional protection.What sets this case apart is the thoughtful integration of a slim wallet – the hidden card slot securely holds my essential cards, minimizing the need for a separate wallet. This minimalist approach is perfect for those who appreciate a streamlined and organized daily carry.In summary, the Nvollnoe iPhone 14 Case with Card Holder is a well-crafted accessory that not only safeguards your device but also adds a touch of practicality with its hidden card slot. It's a stylish and functional choice for anyone looking to simplify their daily essentials

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Ok while it lasted.
reviews.reviewText: So I own both an iPad and an iPhone …. they work for me. Because I have an iPad for most of my big screen stuff, keep my iPhones till they typically stop doing updates for that model phone. Last November my ancient iPhone went belly up and I got a new one with this case.- The case is functional and does protect the phone. Nice!- The slightly raised bevel around the phone prevents the glass from scratching when you place the phone down but doesn’t protect the glass if you put the phone in you pocket with your keys.- The card holder in the back is slightly recessed and has a rubberized bottom of the holder. Two cards work great! Three cards - not so much as the top card often slides out with the sliding cover beginning a 30 second struggle to get the top card.- the case was not very robust though. I dropped it one to many times and fractured the case.The case lasted 11 months. I’m going to look for a new case for my next case.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Paint chips but very durable!
reviews.reviewText: I got this case so I could keep my ID and credit card on me and not have to worry about bringing a purse on a night out. It does fit 2 cards but not more, and sometimes it can be a little hard to get the cards out. However, this case is VERY durable. I got tboned by another car while driving and my phone flew out of the cup holder and got tossed around my car. My phone was completely fine and the case was intact! I still have the case on my phone now. Def worth it

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect fit for my phone.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this for myself. It is so easy to grab and go shopping with just the small strap on your arm and everything you need inside, your money, credit card, phone . Also very attractive.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Compact and does what it’s supposed to
reviews.reviewText: iPhone 14 proI’ve read other reviews that state the buttons on both sides are hard to push. This is true. However, you get used to it very quickly and isn’t an issueThe sliding door “locks” into place with a snap. It isn’t perfect as I’ve seen it unsnap by my handling coming out of my pocket. Never in fear of losing my cards (to date I haven’t dropped it, so I can’t comment on it)In the pocket it’s as slim as a wallet/case combo design can be imo. It’s comfyIt charged with ALL my different wireless chargers I have with the case full of cardsI can easily hold 2 CC’s and one ID. However, if I cut out the rubber insulator behind the case, I can easily add 2 more without losing functionalityFor the price…this fits the bill and is worth the purchaseLike I wrote in the beginning. If I had a gripe…it would be the buttons. They don’t protrude enough, but again, you get used to it
